    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A type of carbon black characterized as a deep, saturated, velvety black color. It is the oldest known black pigment. It is produced by burning oil, usually coal-tar creosote, in shallow pans, in a furnace with the draft regulated to give a heavy smoke cloud.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
